content.text:
Looking at the code, acknowledging an observation just updates two fields in SurrealDB:

```typescript
// observation/queries.ts:67-70
await input.surreal.update(input.observationRecord).merge({
  status: "acknowledged",
  updated_at: input.now,
});
```

That's it — it sets `status` from `"open"` to `"acknowledged"` and updates the timestamp. No side effects, no notifications, no cascading changes.

In the feed, the only visible difference is that an acknowledged observation's action buttons change — it loses the "Acknowledge" button and only shows "Resolve" (from `observationActions` in `feed-route.ts:308-317`).

